{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"a3a1890b-4356-4bf6-b523-7534e72cab2b","agentId":"aac7737a5d3b7d6e7","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are the SIMILARITY AUDITOR for a clean-room process (read /home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/PROTOCOL.md). You may read both sides — that is your function. A prior audit passed the round-1 wellformedness clean crate. Round 2 added new code to /home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/wellformedness/workspace/wf-clean/src/ — specifically: six new checks (Fresh public constants, Reserved prefixes, Left rule, Right rule, Lemma annotations, Multiplication restriction of rules) in checks.rs, a rule pretty-printer (pp_rule/pp_fact_list), a fillSep-style word-wrapper at width 69, indent_block, and diff-mode term/fact projection, plus lib.rs ordering changes.\n\nCompare ONLY those round-2 additions against the GPL originals: /home/kamilner/tamarin-rs/tamarin-prover/lib/theory/src/Theory/Tools/Wellformedness.hs (the diff checks may live in checkWellformednessDiff and helpers; the wrapping in Text/Pretty.hs's fsep usage). Apply abstraction-filtration: identical output strings / behavior / API names given in interface docs are NOT violations; flag internal decomposition mirroring the Haskell where alternatives exist, non-observable names matching Haskell internals, comments echoing Haskell comments, or algorithmic expression matching where observed behavior admits materially different implementations. Also check the round-2 diff-projection logic against the Haskell's getLeftRule/getRightRule/diff projection helpers.\n\nAppend your findings to /home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/wellformedness/AUDIT.md under a \"## Round 2 incremental audit\" heading (per-finding: clean file:line, Haskell file:line, why it survives filtration, behavioral redo instruction). Return a short plain-text verdict: \"pass\" or \"redo\" plus a one-paragraph justification and finding count. Do not modify any other file."},"uuid":"591d5ba4-1522-4247-b0e0-406e11b61ac8","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:16:38.158Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
