{"parentUuid":"da36d9b4-0c64-4c20-b95d-559f9240bc12","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aac7737a5d3b7d6e7","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Cd7czW5qeD87G3LXfW2P6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Db7bCSNuiG8zQ24ye7om85","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/wellformedness/workspace/BEHAVIOR.md","offset":150,"limit":115},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8190,"cache_read_input_tokens":98104,"output_tokens":530,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8190},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":530,"cache_read_input_tokens":98104,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8190,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8190,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Cd7czUb3uoZr2LiS47bGN","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"da9899df-385f-47be-97cf-cd061c8b87dd","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:22:11.922Z","effort":"xhigh","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"da9899df-385f-47be-97cf-cd061c8b87dd","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"a3a1890b-4356-4bf6-b523-7534e72cab2b","agentId":"aac7737a5d3b7d6e7","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Db7bCSNuiG8zQ24ye7om85","type":"tool_result","content":"150\t\n151\t### Fresh public constants (round2; always-on)\n152\tTrigger: a fresh-name literal (`~'foo'`, AST `Term::FreshLit`) used directly in\n153\ta rule. Constants collected in the order premises, conclusions, actions\n154\t(probe fpc_positions). Per rule with >=1 hit, entries joined \"\\n  \\n\":\n155\t    \"  rule `NAME': fresh public constants are not allowed: ~'foo', ~'bar'\"\n156\tconstants rendered by the term printer, \", \" joined. GAP: for a long constant\n157\tlist the oracle word-wraps with a 4-space continuation indent (fpc_positions);\n158\timplementation emits a single line, so byte-parity fixtures use short lists.\n159\t\n160\t### Reserved prefixes (round2; DIFF MODE ONLY)\n161\tTrigger (diff theories only): a fact whose name starts with `DiffIntr` or\n162\t`DiffProto`. Facts collected in the order premises, actions, conclusions\n163\t(probe rp_multi). Per rule the body is:\n164\t    \"  The Rule `NAME' contains facts with reserved prefixes ('DiffIntr',\\n  'DiffProto') inside names:\\n  \\n\" + factblocks\n165\tThe HEADER is word-filled (Wadler `fillSep`) at WIDTH 69, indent 2 (measured via\n166\trp_long/rp_med/rp_w47: a line breaks before the next word once column would\n167\texceed 69). Words treat the rule name `\\`NAME'` and each of `('DiffIntr',` /\n168\t`'DiffProto')` as single tokens. Each factblock (joined \"\\n  \\n\"):\n169\t    \"    <fact_pp>\\n    (ProtoFact <Mult> \\\"<name>\\\" <arity>,<arity>,<Mult>)\"\n170\tThe 2nd line is a raw Haskell Show of a (FactTag, arity, Multiplicity) tuple;\n171\t<Mult> is `Linear`/`Persistent`. GAP: multi-RULE joining unprobed (fixtures use\n172\tone rule).\n173\t\n174\t### Left rule / Right rule (round2; DIFF MODE ONLY)\n175\tTrigger (diff theories only): a diff rule (`Rule.left_right = Some((l,r))`)\n176\twhose explicit `left`/`right` projection differs from the parent rule projected\n177\tto that side (`diff(a,b)` -> a on left, -> b on right). Per rule the LEFT\n178\tprojection is tested first; if inconsistent the RIGHT is not reported for that\n179\trule (probe diff_both: both sides bad -> only \"Left rule\"). Body per entry\n180\t(joined \"\\n  \\n\"):\n181\t    \"  Inconsistent left rule\\n\" + indent4(explicit_rule_pp) +\n182\t    \"\\n  \\n  w.r.t.\\n  \\n\" + indent4(parent_rule_pp)\n183\t(\"left\"/\"right\" and topic \"Left rule\"/\"Right rule\"). Consistency compared via\n184\tthe projected vs. explicit fact lists. Left rule topic precedes Right rule.\n185\t\n186\t### Lemma annotations (round2; always-on)\n187\tTrigger: a lemma with attribute `reuse` AND quantifier `exists-trace` (reuse on\n188\t`all-traces` is fine - probe la_alltraces). Entries joined \"\\n  \\n\":\n189\t    \"  Lemma `NAME': cannot reuse 'exists-trace' lemmas\"\n190\t(Topic may host other annotation conflicts not yet observed.)\n191\t\n192\t### Multiplication restriction of rules (round2; always-on)\n193\tTrigger: a rule whose CONCLUSIONS contain a multiplication (`*`, AST\n194\t`BinOp::Mult`) term. `*` only in premises or only in actions does NOT trigger\n195\t(probes mul_multi, mul_act); a `*` in a premise is not listed even when the\n196\tconclusion also has one (mul_pc). Per rule, entry (joined \"\\n  \\n\"):\n197\t    \"  The following rule is not multiplication restricted:\\n\" + indent4(rule_pp) +\n198\t    \"\\n  \\n  After replacing reducible function symbols in lhs with variables:\\n\" + indent4(rule2_pp) +\n199\t    \"\\n  \\n    Terms with multiplication:  <terms>\"\n200\t<terms> = maximal `*`-subterms of the conclusions, \", \" joined (mul_terms).\n201\tGAPS: (a) rule2 (LHS reducible symbols replaced by fresh vars) is rendered equal\n202\tto rule1 - correct only when the LHS has no reducible symbols (probe mul_exp\n203\tshows `g^c` -> `x.1` otherwise); (b) the alternate failure mode\n204\t\"Variables that occur only in rhs:  <vars>\" (mul_exp) is not implemented; (c)\n205\tthe co-emitted `Message Derivation Checks` block is Maude-derived, OUT OF SCOPE;\n206\t(d) rule_pp wrapping for long rules (see printer note).\n207\t\n208\t### Formula terms\n209\tTrigger: lemma/restriction uses a term that is not a public constant nor a bound\n210\tnode/message variable (free var or reducible function). Body:\n211\t    \"  Lemma `L1' uses terms of the wrong form: `Free y'\\n  \\n\" + fixed_help\n212\tShort single term -> inline; longer/complex -> indented next line\n213\t`    `t1', `t2'` (reducible terms use de Bruijn `Bound N` - gap).\n214\tfixed_help = \"  The only allowed terms are public constants and bound node and\\n  message variables. If you encounter free message variables, then\\n  you might have forgotten a #-prefix. Sort prefixes can only be\\n  dropped where this is unambiguous. Moreover, reducible function\\n  symbols are disallowed.\"\n215\tEntity label `Lemma` or `Restriction`.\n216\t\n217\t### Formula guardedness (topic has LEADING space)\n218\tTrigger: a LEMMA formula not convertible to guarded form. (An unguarded\n219\tRESTRICTION is instead a FATAL error, not a warning -- observed z1; so this\n220\tcheck applies to lemmas only.) Body:\n221\t    \"  Lemma `L2' cannot be converted to a guarded formula:\\n    unguarded variable(s) '#j' in the subformula\\n      \\\"<pp>\\\"\\n    in the formula\\n      \\\"<pp>\\\"\"\n222\t<pp> = unicode formula pretty-print (full printer + guardedness algorithm partial - gap).\n223\t\n224\t### Nat Sorts\n225\tTrigger: var used in %+ (nat) context not of sort nat. Entries joined \"\\n  \\n\":\n226\t    \"  y in term (y%+z) must be of sort nat\" (nat-sort inference - structural only, gap).\n227\t\n228\t### Subterm Convergence Warning\n229\tTrigger: user equation l=r not subterm convergent. Body:\n230\t    \"  User-defined equations must be convergent and have the finite variant property. The following equations are not subterm convergent. If you are sure that the set of equations is nevertheless convergent and has the finite variant property, you can ignore this warning and continue \\n\\n\" + eqs + \"\\n   \\n For more information, please refer to the manual : https://tamarin-prover.com/manual/master/book/010_modeling-issues.html \"\n231\teach eq \"    {lhsPP} = {rhsPP}\" (subterm decision + printer partial - gap).\n232\t\n233\t## Term pretty-printer (observed)\n234\t- Var: sortprefix + base + (\".\"+idx if idx>0). Fresh `~`, Pub `$`, Nat `%`,\n235\t  Node `#`, Msg/Untagged ``.\n236\t- Pair / App(\"pair\",[a,b]): `<a, b, ...>` (right-nested pairs flattened).\n237\t- App(f,args): `f(a, b)` (nullary -> `f`).\n238\t- PubLit s: `'s'`.\n239\t- BinOp: Exp `a^b` (no outer parens); Mult `(a*b)`; Union `(a++b)`;\n240\t  Xor `(a(+)b)` U+2295 AC-sorted; NatPlus `(a%+b)`.\n241\t- NatOne -> `%1`.\n242\t- Fact: [`!` if persistent] + name + \"(\" + (\" \"+args.join(\", \")+\" )\" if args else \" )\").\n243\t\n244\t## Rule pretty-printer (observed; round2)\n245\tUsed by Left/Right rule and Multiplication restriction. Base form (single line\n246\twhen short):\n247\t    \"rule (modulo E) NAME:\\n   [ prems ] <arrow> [ concls ]\"\n248\t- 3-space indent before the fact-list line; fact lists `[ f1, f2 ]`, `[ ]` empty.\n249\t- <arrow> = `-->` (no actions) or `--[ acts ]->` (actions present).\n250\t- `(modulo E)` (the AST modulo field, default \"E\").\n251\t- When embedded in a warning the whole 2-line block is indented (4 for\n252\t  Left/Right and Multiplication, giving 4 and 4+3=7 spaces).\n253\tGAP: long rules wrap - the arrow drops to its own line indented 6 and the\n254\tconclusions to indent 7 (probe mul_terms). Byte-parity fixtures use short rules.\n255\t\n256\t## Formula variable identity (round2 fix)\n257\tFor free-variable detection (Formula terms) and guardedness the oracle treats a\n258\tquantified message variable and its occurrences as ONE variable even when the\n259\tparsed AST tags them with different-but-compatible sorts (Msg vs the Untagged\n260\tdefault; a temporal written `@ i` vs a quantifier `#i`). Matching on the full\n261\tsort tag produced spurious \"Formula terms\"/\" Formula guardedness\" reports on\n262\tround2/exists_trace_reuse (the integration bug). FIX: bind/compare formula\n263\tvariables by NAME only. All prior fixtures (p05, p21, f_subterm) use consistent\n264\tsorts and are unaffected."}]},"uuid":"43c5e840-decc-4f1d-b488-2d8eadb289cc","timestamp":"2026-07-17T12:22:11.947Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-cleanroom/wellformedness/workspace/BEHAVIOR.md","content":"\n### Fresh public constants (round2; always-on)\nTrigger: a fresh-name literal (`~'foo'`, AST `Term::FreshLit`) used directly in\na rule. Constants collected in the order premises, conclusions, actions\n(probe fpc_positions). Per rule with >=1 hit, entries joined \"\\n  \\n\":\n    \"  rule `NAME': fresh public constants are not allowed: ~'foo', ~'bar'\"\nconstants rendered by the term printer, \", \" joined. GAP: for a long constant\nlist the oracle word-wraps with a 4-space continuation indent (fpc_positions);\nimplementation emits a single line, so byte-parity fixtures use short lists.\n\n### Reserved prefixes (round2; DIFF MODE ONLY)\nTrigger (diff theories only): a fact whose name starts with `DiffIntr` or\n`DiffProto`. Facts collected in the order premises, actions, conclusions\n(probe rp_multi). Per rule the body is:\n    \"  The Rule `NAME' contains facts with reserved prefixes ('DiffIntr',\\n  'DiffProto') inside names:\\n  \\n\" + factblocks\nThe HEADER is word-filled (Wadler `fillSep`) at WIDTH 69, indent 2 (measured via\nrp_long/rp_med/rp_w47: a line breaks before the next word once column would\nexceed 69). Words treat the rule name `\\`NAME'` and each of `('DiffIntr',` /\n`'DiffProto')` as single tokens. Each factblock (joined \"\\n  \\n\"):\n    \"    <fact_pp>\\n    (ProtoFact <Mult> \\\"<name>\\\" <arity>,<arity>,<Mult>)\"\nThe 2nd line is a raw Haskell Show of a (FactTag, arity, Multiplicity) tuple;\n<Mult> is `Linear`/`Persistent`. GAP: multi-RULE joining unprobed (fixtures use\none rule).\n\n### Left rule / Right rule (round2; DIFF MODE ONLY)\nTrigger (diff theories only): a diff rule (`Rule.left_right = Some((l,r))`)\nwhose explicit `left`/`right` projection differs from the parent rule projected\nto that side (`diff(a,b)` -> a on left, -> b on right). Per rule the LEFT\nprojection is tested first; if inconsistent the RIGHT is not reported for that\nrule (probe diff_both: both sides bad -> only \"Left rule\"). Body per entry\n(joined \"\\n  \\n\"):\n    \"  Inconsistent left rule\\n\" + indent4(explicit_rule_pp) +\n    \"\\n  \\n  w.r.t.\\n  \\n\" + indent4(parent_rule_pp)\n(\"left\"/\"right\" and topic \"Left rule\"/\"Right rule\"). Consistency compared via\nthe projected vs. explicit fact lists. Left rule topic precedes Right rule.\n\n### Lemma annotations (round2; always-on)\nTrigger: a lemma with attribute `reuse` AND quantifier `exists-trace` (reuse on\n`all-traces` is fine - probe la_alltraces). Entries joined \"\\n  \\n\":\n    \"  Lemma `NAME': cannot reuse 'exists-trace' lemmas\"\n(Topic may host other annotation conflicts not yet observed.)\n\n### Multiplication restriction of rules (round2; always-on)\nTrigger: a rule whose CONCLUSIONS contain a multiplication (`*`, AST\n`BinOp::Mult`) term. `*` only in premises or only in actions does NOT trigger\n(probes mul_multi, mul_act); a `*` in a premise is not listed even when the\nconclusion also has one (mul_pc). Per rule, entry (joined \"\\n  \\n\"):\n    \"  The following rule is not multiplication restricted:\\n\" + indent4(rule_pp) +\n    \"\\n  \\n  After replacing reducible function symbols in lhs with variables:\\n\" + indent4(rule2_pp) +\n    \"\\n  \\n    Terms with multiplication:  <terms>\"\n<terms> = maximal `*`-subterms of the conclusions, \", \" joined (mul_terms).\nGAPS: (a) rule2 (LHS reducible symbols replaced by fresh vars) is rendered equal\nto rule1 - correct only when the LHS has no reducible symbols (probe mul_exp\nshows `g^c` -> `x.1` otherwise); (b) the alternate failure mode\n\"Variables that occur only in rhs:  <vars>\" (mul_exp) is not implemented; (c)\nthe co-emitted `Message Derivation Checks` block is Maude-derived, OUT OF SCOPE;\n(d) rule_pp wrapping for long rules (see printer note).\n\n### Formula terms\nTrigger: lemma/restriction uses a term that is not a public constant nor a bound\nnode/message variable (free var or reducible function). Body:\n    \"  Lemma `L1' uses terms of the wrong form: `Free y'\\n  \\n\" + fixed_help\nShort single term -> inline; longer/complex -> indented next line\n`    `t1', `t2'` (reducible terms use de Bruijn `Bound N` - gap).\nfixed_help = \"  The only allowed terms are public constants and bound node and\\n  message variables. If you encounter free message variables, then\\n  you might have forgotten a #-prefix. Sort prefixes can only be\\n  dropped where this is unambiguous. Moreover, reducible function\\n  symbols are disallowed.\"\nEntity label `Lemma` or `Restriction`.\n\n### Formula guardedness (topic has LEADING space)\nTrigger: a LEMMA formula not convertible to guarded form. (An unguarded\nRESTRICTION is instead a FATAL error, not a warning -- observed z1; so this\ncheck applies to lemmas only.) Body:\n    \"  Lemma `L2' cannot be converted to a guarded formula:\\n    unguarded variable(s) '#j' in the subformula\\n      \\\"<pp>\\\"\\n    in the formula\\n      \\\"<pp>\\\"\"\n<pp> = unicode formula pretty-print (full printer + guardedness algorithm partial - gap).\n\n### Nat Sorts\nTrigger: var used in %+ (nat) context not of sort nat. Entries joined \"\\n  \\n\":\n    \"  y in term (y%+z) must be of sort nat\" (nat-sort inference - structural only, gap).\n\n### Subterm Convergence Warning\nTrigger: user equation l=r not subterm convergent. Body:\n    \"  User-defined equations must be convergent and have the finite variant property. The following equations are not subterm convergent. If you are sure that the set of equations is nevertheless convergent and has the finite variant property, you can ignore this warning and continue \\n\\n\" + eqs + \"\\n   \\n For more information, please refer to the manual : https://tamarin-prover.com/manual/master/book/010_modeling-issues.html \"\neach eq \"    {lhsPP} = {rhsPP}\" (subterm decision + printer partial - gap).\n\n## Term pretty-printer (observed)\n- Var: sortprefix + base + (\".\"+idx if idx>0). Fresh `~`, Pub `$`, Nat `%`,\n  Node `#`, Msg/Untagged ``.\n- Pair / App(\"pair\",[a,b]): `<a, b, ...>` (right-nested pairs flattened).\n- App(f,args): `f(a, b)` (nullary -> `f`).\n- PubLit s: `'s'`.\n- BinOp: Exp `a^b` (no outer parens); Mult `(a*b)`; Union `(a++b)`;\n  Xor `(a(+)b)` U+2295 AC-sorted; NatPlus `(a%+b)`.\n- NatOne -> `%1`.\n- Fact: [`!` if persistent] + name + \"(\" + (\" \"+args.join(\", \")+\" )\" if args else \" )\").\n\n## Rule pretty-printer (observed; round2)\nUsed by Left/Right rule and Multiplication restriction. Base form (single line\nwhen short):\n    \"rule (modulo E) NAME:\\n   [ prems ] <arrow> [ concls ]\"\n- 3-space indent before the fact-list line; fact lists `[ f1, f2 ]`, `[ ]` empty.\n- <arrow> = `-->` (no actions) or `--[ acts ]->` (actions present).\n- `(modulo E)` (the AST modulo field, default \"E\").\n- When embedded in a warning the whole 2-line block is indented (4 for\n  Left/Right and Multiplication, giving 4 and 4+3=7 spaces).\nGAP: long rules wrap - the arrow drops to its own line indented 6 and the\nconclusions to indent 7 (probe mul_terms). Byte-parity fixtures use short rules.\n\n## Formula variable identity (round2 fix)\nFor free-variable detection (Formula terms) and guardedness the oracle treats a\nquantified message variable and its occurrences as ONE variable even when the\nparsed AST tags them with different-but-compatible sorts (Msg vs the Untagged\ndefault; a temporal written `@ i` vs a quantifier `#i`). Matching on the full\nsort tag produced spurious \"Formula terms\"/\" Formula guardedness\" reports on\nround2/exists_trace_reuse (the integration bug). FIX: bind/compare formula\nvariables by NAME only. All prior fixtures (p05, p21, f_subterm) use consistent\nsorts and are unaffected.","numLines":115,"startLine":150,"totalLines":274}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"da9899df-385f-47be-97cf-cd061c8b87dd","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/kamilner/tamarin-rs","sessionId":"57f8e1bc-d495-4b36-93c0-033347d5034a","version":"2.1.212","gitBranch":"main"}
